# Blocks are organised into 'block groups'.
# To start a group, start a line with `=`, optionally followed by a name.
# To end a group, simply have a line with only a `=`.

= my daily blocks
# Constrain your blocks on a schedule by starting a line with `@`. This constraint will
# block the group from 12:00 until 13:00, every day.
@ 12:00 - 13:00
# You can have multiple constraints, but they can't overlap.
#
# You can make time spans 'wrap around' midnight too. For instance, this constraint will
# leave the group *un*blocked from 06:00 until 18:00.
@ 18:00 - 06:00

# List of sites to block. "www." variants are added automatically.
reddit.com
facebook.com
twitter.com
=


= my weekly blocks
# You can make weekday-based constraints too, via (some unique prefix of) their names.
# Like the time-only constraints, these shouldn't overlap.
@ mon 00:00 - fri 23:59
@ sat 20:00 - sat 23:59

# You can have time-only & day-based constraints at the same time.
@ 23:00 - 06:00

youtube.com
twitch.tv
=


= durational blocks
# You can specify that a group can be unblocked for a certain duration per
# day/week/month by starting the line with a `<`. You can only have one duration-based
# constraint on a group.
#
# Duration-based blocks can either be `per` day/week/month, or `each` day/week/month:
#
# * *per* means they'll reset after that amount of time since the previous reset (eg.
#   `per week` will reset every 24×7 hours).
# * *each* means they'll reset after that quantity ticks over on the calendar (eg. `each
#   month` will reset when the calendar month has changed).
#
# Duration-based blocks are activated and deactivated via the CLI.
<1hrs per week

zombo.com
=


= combo blocks
# You can have a duration-based *and* schedule-based constraint on the same group. In
# this case, the group can only be deactivated when the schedule would be open.
#
# At the point the schedule constraints open up, a group that also has a duration-based
# constraint won't automatically become unblocked: it needs to be specifically unblocked
# via the CLI.
<1.5hrs each day
@ 00:00 - 17:00

tumblr.com
=
